@node DEVE "PlugIn Manager"

This the window where you install/uninstall your PlugIns.

@{u}Installation of a PlugIn@{uu}
When you want to install a new PlugIn into Apache's PlugIn menu
press the Add button. A filerequester opens. Now navigate to
the directory of the PlugIn you want to install. Select the
file @{b}Apache.PlugIn@{ub}.

The selected PlugIn now appears in the listview gadget telling
you what the PlugIn is for and the version number.

Press the @{b}Okay@{ub} button and you're done. The new PlugIn
will now appear in the PlugIn menu.

The @{b}Delete@{ub} button deletes the current active entry. Note
that it is only the entry that is deleted and not the PlugIn files
on your disk!

@{u}Sorting the entries@{uu}
You can use drag'n'drop to change the ordering of the entries in the
listview gadget.

@{u}Enable/disable AutoStart@{uu}
Double click on an entry to toggle the AutoStart mode ON/OFF.

@endnode

@node PREF "Settings"

@{u}The Settings window@{uu}

 · @{b}Author@{ub}. Enter your name here. Your name will be saved together with
   the files saved by the PlugIns.

 @{u}Piano@{uu}

 · @{b}Auto Open Piano@{ub}. The Piano window will open automagically when
   you start Apache if this checkmark is checked.
   
 · @{b}Octaves@{ub}. Number of octaves for Piano window. Any changes you make 
   here will first take effect the next time you start Apache. (Sorry)

 · @{b}Size@{ub}. The size of the tangents in the Piano window. Any changes you 
   make here will first take effect the next time you start Apache. (Sorry)

 @{u}MIDI@{uu}
    
 · @{b}Device@{ub}. The device name of your MIDI interface. Any changes you make 
   here will first take effect the next time you start Apache. (Sorry)

 · @{b}SysEx Buffer@{ub}. The size of the buffer used in the @{" SysEx " link WIN_SYSEX} window.
   Buffer size can be anything from 1K to 150K.
 
 · @{b}MIDI Echo@{ub}. If checked Apache will echo all incoming MIDI data to the 
   MIDI out port.
 
 · @{b}Real Time Update@{ub}. If checked the PlugIn modules will send changes to 
   their MIDI devices as soon as you change some of the patch parameters.

@{u}How to setup on which screen Apache opens@{uu}
Apache uses MUI and therefore you use MUI to select then screen Apache opens on.
You can use the program called @{b}PSI@{ub} that comes with MUI to create a
screen of your choice and then you select the MUI menu item in the Apache menu
to start the MUI-preferences program for Apache. Here you select the screen
Apache opens on. You can also start @{b}PSI@{ub} from here.

Consult the MUI documentation for more information.

@endnode

@node INST "Installation"

Installation is quite simple - use the supplied installer script. 

Apache will not scatter files all over your HD. Everything is contained
within the Apache directory and its subdirs..
@endnode

