@endnode

@node WIN_SYSEX "SysEx Manager"

This window is not finished yet. Record is not implemented but you can load
SysEx dumps and send them over the MIDI port or save them to disk.

You can load as many SysEx dumps that will fit in the buffer.

The buffer size can be adjusted in the @{" Settings " link PREF} window.

@endnode

@node HISTORY "Program history"

 Program history - a description of each release. Note: I use
 C='s definition of version numbers. Ex. 1.10 is newer than 1.5!
 In fact every time I make a change in the sourcecode and I compile
 Apache the version number gets increased by one!

 I use the following 3 letter IDs to describe changes:

   FIX - Bug fix
   NEW - New feature
   CHG - Change in behaviour from previous versions

 @{u}History (Newest on top)@{uu}

  @{b}v1.124 - 2 Sep 1996@{ub}
   FIX · "Add PlugIn" function was broken.
   FIX · Load and save requesters in SysEx manager window were broken.
   FIX · Clicking on the rightmost pixel in the piano gadget caused an
         extra key to show up.

  @{b}v1.122 - 21 Jul 1996@{ub}
   FIX · Fixed the background in the "status" text gadget in the SysEx 
         manager.
   NEW · Auto start feature for the PlugIns. Check out the PlugIn manager!
   NEW · Made some enhancements to Apache.library. You can now <ESC> the
         "Enter number" and "Enter range" windows + made support for
         multi-selection in the filerequester functions

  @{b}v1.109 - 26 May 1996@{ub}
   NEW · SysEx manager. Not 100% done though..
   CHG · Cursor keys in Piano window now goes one octave up/down
         instead of selecting high/low octave mode
   NEW · Configurable number of octaves for Piano
   NEW · Configurable size for Piano window
   CHG · When you add a new PlugIn the default directory is "PlugIns/"
   CHG · Change in MIDI code. SysEx messages will not be echoed.
   NEW · You can now grab and release the MIDI port using the menu.
   CHG · Apache will start up if it cannot grab MIDI port.
   NEW · Cancel button in PlugIn manager window
   NEW · Some internal changes in the communication between Apache and
         the PlugIns.
   NEW · PlugIns can now refuse quitting if you try to quit Apache but
         a PlugIn doesn't want to (ex. has unsaved changes)

  @{b}v1.38 - 2 Apr 1996@{ub}
   NEW · Drag'n'drop support in PlugIn manager
   NEW · Added PlugIn installation info to the docs
   NEW · Progress-windows now also show % done
   FIX · Cosmetic change in piano window. More space on the right edge.

  @{b}v1.0 - 17 Mar 1996@{ub}
    First release.
 
@endnode

